KG name: DATATURCYL - LOD for tourists in Castilla y León (Spain)
Description: The aim of this project- called DATATURCYL- is to reuse and redistribute open data provided by the Junta de Castilla y León to enrich and enhance information services about tourism in the community. To provide them with an added value- this project embraces the Linked Open Data philosophy. In our particular case- the information for tourism (bars- restaurants- hotels- etc.) is converted to RDF and enriched with geographic data sources and open knowledge in Dbpedia.
